---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Open Source | Chouhan Industries | Hardware in the Open"
  ogTitle="Open Source | Chouhan Industries"
  description="Every schematic, tolerance spec, and process document is public record. No proprietary lock-in. No licensing walls."
  url="https://chouhan.ai/open-source.html"
>

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Open by Default</p>
      <h1>Open <em>Source</em></h1>
      <p class="page-sub">Every schematic, tolerance spec, and process document is public record. No proprietary
        lock-in. No licensing walls.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="os-grid">
        <div class="os-item">
          <h3>Repository</h3>
          <p>All design files, schematics, and hardware documentation live on GitHub. Fork it, study it, improve it.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/animesh-chouhan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link">View on
            GitHub</a>
        </div>
        <div class="os-item">
          <h3>Contributing</h3>
          <p>We welcome contributions from engineers, manufacturers, and researchers. Open a pull request or raise an
            issue. All discussion is public.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/animesh-chouhan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="link">Contribution Guide</a>
        </div>
        <div class="os-item">
          <h3>Documentation</h3>
          <p>Manufacturing tolerances, assembly processes, materials specifications, all published alongside the design
            files. Nothing withheld.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/animesh-chouhan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link">Read the
            Docs</a>
        </div>
        <div class="os-item">
          <h3>Release Policy</h3>
          <p>Design files are published before units ship. We do not release a product without first publishing
            everything needed to reproduce it independently.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="license-block">
        <h3>CERN Open Hardware License v2.0 (Strongly Reciprocal)</h3>
        <p>All hardware designs are released under CERN OHL-S v2.0. This means anyone can use, study, modify, and
          distribute the designs, provided that any modifications are also released under the same license. The work
          stays open, permanently.</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 12px;">
          <a href="https://ohwr.org/project/cernohl/-/wikis/uploads/819d71bea3458f71fba6cf4fb0f2de6b/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt"
            target="_blank" rel="license noopener noreferrer" class="link">Read the full license</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <p class="section-label">What Is Open Source Hardware?</p>
      <p
        style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--muted); max-width: 640px; margin-bottom: 24px;">
        This video describes the attributes of open source hardware to the general public. Officially released by the
        Open Source Hardware Association.
      </p>
      <a href="https://oshwa.org/resources/open-source-hardware-definition/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="role-apply" style="display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 48px;">Learn More</a>
      <div class="video-embed">
        <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9xGRaPrcvVg?si=qM7CEtjqrNXDV5_I"
          title="What Is Open Source Hardware?" frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section surface">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <p class="section-label">Why open source</p>
      <p
        style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.6vw, 1.3rem); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--text); opacity: 0.75; max-width: 760px;">
        Open source is the way forward because transparency scales better than trust. Closed systems ask you to
        believe. Open ones let you verify, which means faster bug discovery, stronger security, and compounding
        innovation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
